In addition, it has long been mastered the technology necessary to convert it into energy, including high yield charring, gasification and synthetic fuel liquefaction.
This technology is widely used during World War II, has seen considerable progress since.
The biomass energy is, however, a victim of unfair competition from fossil fuels.
