The psychology of overbidding why more money is spent?
At auctions, buyers tend to spend more, and overestimate the goods.
Researchers in neurology and New York University economics managed to update the neurological and economic foundations of this known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to their study published in the journal Science, human beings do not want to be left behind in this type of competition, such as an auction on eBay, and that is why they even prefer to pay too high a price.
This research has attempted to draw a neurological scheme of this kind of "game" using experimental auctions.
A volunteer groups playing the lottery, while the other group took part in an auction playful auctions, while at using a functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI), researchers analyzed the brain areas active experimental subjects.
In both games, the participants could earn money, but during the auction an essential element is outbid by a third, all located in the brain stem, called the striatum, began to move in intensive way when losing the game.
This part of the brain, next to several other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of "self - stimulation" of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to the researchers, the rise in prices is due to the flight from the violent reaction of the striatum.
In support of their theories, economists members of this group of researchers have pursued Financial Supervisory analyzes.
When those - one, three groups surench√©rissaient facing a partner in various circumstances.
They simply informed of the actual value of the control group product, and they have thus made their money.
In another group, they promised that if, in addition, they emerged winner of the game, then they would receive an additional $ 15 in reward.
While the third group he received the $ 15 prior to the auction, but the group members also were losing money in case they lost the auction.
The difference between these two groups is that the focus was at one with the victory, while in the other, about the failure.
In proving the hypothesis neurologists, the members of the team players "against failure" were willing to put higher than those made by the control group and the group "for the win."
"These results can not be demonstrated by any existing economic theory.
Indeed, each of them explaining the phenomena observed during auctions by the pleasure of winning and the parade in front of the risk.
Only neuroimaging methods have helped to remove the contradiction between the two leading theories now on a third explanation. "- Noted Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics of the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when should - we see a doctor?
Worldwide, about half a billion people suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, while in Hungary, the chronic liver disease is mentioned among the top causes of death.
The patients carrying the hepatitis hundred miles is estimated in Hungary, but only seven miles in treatment. This is due to the fact that patients often do not know they are infected.
The hepatitis name is generic name given to infections affecting the liver and caused by different viruses.
There are many similarities between their symptoms. Inflammation of the liver and jaundice are characteristic, but pathogens and diseases caused differ from each other.
The hepatitis virus, according to the pathogenic genes are spread mainly in two forms: hepatitis A and E through the digestive tract (eg, contaminated food or water), hepatitis B, C, D, and other viruses by blood and body fluids (semen, vaginal secretions, saliva).
For travelers, it is anyway recommended to be vaccinated against influenza A and B. There is no vaccine against the C ..
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after eating contaminated food, usually accompanied by malaise, weakness, stomach pain and nausea.
Then develops on the skin and the white of the eye visible jaundice, stools become clearer and urine to be darker color. Healing can take two to three weeks.
Around the world, every year one million people die from the most severe form of this disease, such as cancer or liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B ..
The main reason is that according to estimates, only ten patients receiving medical treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have serious consequences if left untreated, it can lead to cirrhosis or liver cancer.
Most patients do not know have the virus because the pathogenic gene sneaky way destroys liver cells. In many cases, the first symptoms appear only after 20 to 30 years.
Therefore, an early warning is very significant, and regular testing.
The contamination is much higher than average among a population of three groups: those who underwent blood transfusion before 1991, drug users and tattooed.
Currently, amounts to 200 million patients with chronic hepatitis type C in the world.
Since the disease can be detected by a routine laboratory examination, it is advisable to consult your doctor as soon observation of unknown origin symptoms.
The disease can be cured if detected in time. The virus can be eradicated from the body, in this way the risk of contagion disappears and the development of cancer is prevented.
September 30 is World Hepatitis Day, organized for the first time in 2004 by the organizations representing patients from around the world.
Its aim is to draw attention to chronic liver cirrhosis caused by viruses, the causes of its development and the importance of early diagnosis of the disease.
